-Numerous experiments demonstrating genetic variance in almost any trait, can safely assume presence of genetic variance in any metric character
-**most genetic correlations are positive, but correlations among life history traits tend to be negative, more so than among physiological or morphological traits (Roff 1996)

COMMENTS FOR PRESENTATION

-slide #2 - Numerous experiments demonstrating genetic variance in almost any trait, can safely assume presence of genetic variance in any metric character (lynch & walsh 1998, brakefield 2003)
-slide #4 - genetic correlations not absolute contraint unless they are perfect, for if not, then some variance exists in direction accessible to selection, hence some response is expected

