-Kingsolver et al 2001 - more comments on correlational selection and a possibly good review
-Blows et al 2004, Hine et al 2004, 2009, Van Homrigh et al 2007, Hunt et al 2007 - case studies with sexual selection and organism responses 

TERMS
-"correlational selection" is a form of natural selection that favors certain combinations of traits (phenotypic integration). It can promote both genetic correlations and high levels of genetic variation.
-"index selection" is a method of artificial selection in which several useful traits are selected simultaneously. First, each trait that is going to be selected is assigned a weight - the importance of the trait.
